                <h1>How Long Do Misdemeanors Remain on Your Record?</h1>
                <p>Misdemeanors typically stay on your criminal record indefinitely, unless you take steps to expunge or seal them. Depending on the state, the waiting period for expungement can range from a few years to over a decade. Itâ€™s essential to understand your local laws, as they vary significantly, impacting employment and housing opportunities.</p>
